{"first_name":"Hal","last_name":"Danziger","permalink":"hal-danziger","crunchbase_url":"http://www.crunchbase.com/person/hal-danziger","homepage_url":"http://www.linkedin.com/pub/dir/hal/danziger","birthplace":"Dix Hills, NY","twitter_username":null,"blog_url":"http://halwebguy.danziger.net","blog_feed_url":"http://twitter.com/statuses/user_timeline/14121778.rss","affiliation_name":"CBS","born_year":1995,"born_month":5,"born_day":3,"tag_list":"content-management, cms, media, online-media, digital-media, product, technology","alias_list":null,"created_at":"Tue Jan 20 23:32:40 UTC 2009","updated_at":"Mon Jan 30 18:25:06 UTC 2012","overview":"<p>Hal Danziger is the Chief Technology Officer at New York Media LLC, where he is responsible for web development, infrastructure, and other facets of technology.  New York Media publishes New York Magazine, nymag.com, menupages.com, grubstreet.com and vulture.com.</p>\n\n<p>Previously, Hal served as VP, Product Management at CBS Television Stations Digital Media.  In this role, he oversaw the features for the owned and operated CBS television stations&#8217; web sites.  This includes wcbstv.com in New York, cbs2.com in Los Angeles, in addition to about 20 other television station web sites.  </p>\n\n<p>Prior to this role, Danziger served as Director of Development for the group, where he led application development efforts to build and roll-out a home-grown content management system, and all of their web sites. </p>\n\n<p>While working for Cablevision, Danziger designed and implemented solutions for their Digital Asset Management System, among other set-top box projects.  </p>\n\n<p>He has also served in CTO and Director of Development roles for web development companies, where he&#8217;s architected and guided solutions for companies including PRNewswire, Nortel Networks, and Cablevision Systems Corp.</p>","image":{"available_sizes":[[[150,150],"assets/images/resized/0003/4401/34401v2-max-150x150.jpg"],[[178,178],"assets/images